ped Basculin have the same two standard possible Abilities as red-striped Basculin—{{a|Reckless}} and {{a|Adaptability}} (and is listed as such in [[Pokédex 3D]]); however, the blue-striped Basculin that can be obtained via in-game trade in White has the Ability {{a|Rock Head}}. In Pokémon Black 2 and White 2, wild blue-striped Basculin\'s two standard possible Abilities are {{a|Rock Head}} and {{a|Adaptability}}, while red-striped Basculin\'s stay the same (and are listed as such in [[Pokédex 3D Pro]]). However, blue-striped Basculin [[Pokémon breeding|bred]] in Pokémon Black 2 and White 2 have Reckless and Adaptability as their two standard Abilities. When a blue-striped Basculin with Reckless is transferred from [[Generation V]] to [[Generation VI]], its Ability is changed to Rock Head.\n* Basculin shares its {{pkmn|category}} with {{p|Zweilous}}. They are both known as the Hostile Pokémon.\n* Basculin\'s Pokédex entries in {{game|Black and White|s 2|Pokémon Black 2, White 2}}, [[Pokémon X and Y|X]], and [[Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire|Omega Ruby]] describe the species as being very tasty, one of the rare instances that hint at Pokémon being used for food.\n\n===Origin===\nBasculin were most likely inspired by a {{wp|bass (fish)|bass}} or {{wp|piranha}}, the latter of which has historically been viewed as violent.\n\nAccording to interviews with [[Ken Sugimori]] in \'\'Nintendo Dream\'\', Basculin was created late in development when they realized there were few new \'standard\' fish-like Pokémon in Unova, the only others being {{p|Alomomola}}, {{p|Stunfisk}}, {{p|Frillish}}, and {{p|Jellicent}}. It was given two forms to make up for the small amount of fish in the region, and it was also based on a bass since there are wild bass in {{wp|New York (state)|New York}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nBasculin is a combination of \'\'bass\'\' and \'\'masculine\'\'.\n\nBassrao may be a combination of \'\'bass\'\' and 丈夫 \'\'masurao\'\' (warrior, referring to its {{a|Reckless|bold, violent nature}}) or バカラオ \'\'bakarao\'\' ({{wp|bacalhau}}).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Water|type2=Water\n|ja=バスラオ \'\'Bassrao\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'bass\'\' and {{tt|丈夫 \'\'masurao\'\'|warrior, referring to its bold, violent nature}} or {{tt|バカラオ \'\'bakarao\'\'|bacalhau}}\n|de=Barschuft|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Barsch|perch}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|Schuft|rascal}}\'\'\n|fr=Bargantua|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|bar|bass}}\'\' and {{wp|Gargantua and Pantagruel|\'\'Gargantua\'\'}}, a powerful giant in French literature\n|es=Basculin|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Basculin|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=배쓰나이 \'\'Bessnai\'\'|komeaning=From \'\'bass\'\' and {{tt|사나이 \'\'sana\'i\'\'|man, hombre, bro (informal)}}; may also be based on {{tt|사나이다움 \'\'sana\'ida\'um\'\'|masculinity, manhood, machismo}} or {{tt|사나이다운 \'\'sana\'ida\'un\'\'|macho, strongly masculine}}.\n|zh_yue=野蠻鱸魚 \'\'Yéhmàahnlòuhyú\'\'{{tt|*|Games}}<br>勇士鱸魚 \'\'Yúhngsihlòuhyú\'\'{{tt|*|Anime, manga}}|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|野蠻 \'\'yéhmàahn\'\'|savage}} and {{tt|鱸魚 \'\'lòuhyú\'\'|bass}}<br>From {{tt|勇士 \'\'yúhngsih\'\'|warrior}} and {{tt|鱸魚 \'\'lòuhyú\'\'|bass}}\n|zh_cmn=野蠻鱸魚 / 野蛮鲈鱼 \'\'Yěmánlúyú\'\'{{tt|*|Games}}<br>勇士鱸魚 / 勇士鲈鱼 \'\'Yǒngshìlúyú\'\'{{tt|*|Anime, manga}}|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|野蠻 \'\'yěmán\'\'|savage}} and {{tt|鱸魚 \'\'lúyú\'\'|bass}}<br>From {{tt|勇士 \'\'yǒngshì\'\'|warrior}} and {{tt|鱸魚 \'\'lúyú\'\'|bass}}\n|ru=Баскулин \'\'Baskulin\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n{| style="float:left"\n|-\n| style="vertical-align:top" |\n\'\'Red-Striped Form\'\'\n{{langtable|color={{water color}}|bordercolor={{red color dark}}\n|ja=あかすじのすがた \'\'Red-Striped Form\'\'\n|zh_yue=紅條紋的樣子 \'\'{{tt|Hùhngtìuhmàhn-dīk Yeuhngjí|Red-Striped Form}}\'\' {{tt|*|Games}}\n|zh_cmn=紅條紋的樣子 / 红条纹的样子 \'\'{{tt|Hóngtiáowén-de Yàngzi|Red-Striped Form}}\'\' {{tt|*|Games}}<br>紅線 \'\'{{tt|Hóngxiàn|Red Stripe}}\'\' {{tt|*|Anime, manga}}\n|es=Forma Raya Roja\n|fr=Motif Rouge\n|de=Rotlinige Form\n|it=Forma Linearossa\n|ko=적색근의 모습 \'\'Red-Striped Form\'\'\n|pl=Forma Czerwono Paskowana}}\n| style="vertical-align:top" |\n\'\'Blue-Striped Form\'\'\n{{langtable|color={{water color}}|bordercolor={{blue color dark}}\n|ja=あおすじのすがた \'\'Blue-Striped Form\'\'\n|zh_yue=藍條紋的樣子 \'\'{{tt|Làahmtìuhmàhn-dīk Yeuhngjí|Blue-Striped Form}}\'\' {{tt|*|Games}}\n|zh_cmn=藍條紋的樣子 / 蓝条纹的样子 \'\'{{tt|Lántiáowén-de Yàngzi|Blue-Striped Form}}\'\' {{tt|*|Games}}<br>藍線 \'\'{{tt|Lánxiàn|Blue Stripe}}\'\' {{tt|*|Anime, manga}}\n|es=Forma Raya Azul\n|fr=Motif Bleu\n|de=Blaulinige Form\n|it=Forma Lineablu\n|ko=청색근의 모습 \'\'Blue-Striped Form\'\'\n|pl=Forma Niebiesko Paskowana}}\n|}{{-}}\n<!--\n==Notes==\n<references />-->\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Water}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Water|prevnum=549|prev=Lilligant|nextnum=551|next=Sandile}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:F.E.A.R.-compatible Pokémon]]\n\n[[de:Barschuft]]\n[[es:Basculin]]\n[[fr:Bargantua]]\n[[it:Basculin]]\n[[ja:バスラオ]]\n[[zh:野蛮鲈鱼]]'}